                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1165.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Foreign Office has just forwarded to this Legation a copy of a decree dated April
                    29, declaring a blockade against Fort Liberté and Cape Haitien. At present it is
                    not effective as both <hi rend="italic">Pacifique</hi> and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Nord Alexis</hi> were here until this morning when they sailed carrying
                    troops; destination supposed to be Gonaives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
